Reasoning: many services show simultaneous gRPC/HTTP latency rises and downstream request-counts/success-rates falling — consistent with either network packet issues (loss/retransmits or increased network latency) or resource exhaustion (CPU) causing timeouts. To disambiguate, check:
- container network retransmits (e.g., container.net.tcp_retrans_segs) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- container network packet drop/error counters (interface Rx/Tx errors) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- container/network RTT metrics (per-flow rtt) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- container CPU usage (container.cpu.*) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
and run a collect_trace on the slow checkoutservice call chain to see TCP retransmits/timeouts vs CPU-stalled stacks.
